Label: abdomen element
Definition: An organ or element that is in the abdomen. Examples: spleen, intestine, kidney, abdominal mammary gland.

Label: liver
Definition: An exocrine gland which secretes bile and functions in metabolism of protein and carbohydrate and fat, synthesizes substances involved in the clotting of the blood, synthesizes vitamin A, detoxifies poisonous substances, stores glycogen, and breaks down worn-out erythrocytes.
